      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>5 threads, <a href=item.html?item=20366&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105958781314042>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=20366&mid=105958781314042>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=20366&mid=105958781314042>Really a bard weapon?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=20366&mid=105958781314042#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 30th 2:04 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=195083><span id= >stacnmae</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At first look you would say that this is definitely a Bard weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;But in reality it is unlikely that a lot of bards will get one.  The one element of this weapon that screams bard is the brass instrument modifier.  Well as it turns out if your a bard in a guild that can kill the MoR you more than likely have your epic.  The brass instrument modifier on epic is the same.  Without the instrument modifier being a factor all of a sudden it becomes a ranger weapon (at least thats what the rangers think).<br><br>When my guild killed MoR this dropped and there was quite a heated conversation as to whether the bard should get it or not.  At the end of the day a ranger got the weapon because bard had an epic.  <br><br>So thank you again Verant for putting more bard usable items out there that a bard will more than likely never get because &quot;another class can use it better&quot;.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
