	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=226409><span id= >kniedzw</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The modifier on Marrow's Song is 2.0, compared with the epic's 1.8, so the modifier isn't quite the same.&nbsp;&nbsp;Moreover, the additional stats point more toward a bard (since high Cha reduces fizzles), but it's perfectly reasonable for a guild to reward this to another class, as the ratio is quite good.<br><br>SoE has lately pushed toward making items with instrument modifiers usable by more classes than just bards; look, for instance, at the Eye of Dreams, which has a 2.2 brass modifier but is ALL/ALL with stats that most people would find desirable.<br><br>I'm actually in favor of this, as it is a too-frequent occurance that I see class-specific loot rot because the classes in question present have the item (or better) already.  It's understandable that there would be some dissatisfaction with Sony's decisions, though.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
