	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=20366&mid=106252309760421>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=20366&mid=106252309760421>RE: This was the %$#@</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=20366&mid=106252309760421#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Sep 2nd 1:21 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35083><span id=Scholar>Nocturne</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>22 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The new version of Hate actually makes it *much, much* easier for Rangers and Mages to get their epic pieces.<br><br>The minibosses that drop epic components for these two classes now have placeholders that repop roughly every 30 minutes.&nbsp;&nbsp;So now, instead of having to port an entire raid up there only to find out that there are no minibosses up, you can port up a single group (safely, I might add) and kill placeholders until the bosses spawn.<br><br>Also, thanks to mob placement and pathing changes, it's now *much* easier to pull singles (even a warrior can pull a mob up there with only one or two adds), which means that crowd-control isn't the absolute necessity that it once was.<br><br>The minibosses that drop the Ranger and Mage pieces spawn in &quot;Tier 1&quot; areas, which means that the mobs you'll be fighting are exactly the same difficulty as the old Hate, except without the huge risk of chain-aggro.<br><br>Also, because there is no 2nd floor anymore, there's no need for people to camp out if they happen to get Grav Fluxxed (I haven't seen a mob use this at all since the change, but I wouldn't rule it out as a possibility).<br><br>Even Warriors and Enchanters have a slightly easier time getting their epic drops now.  To get the warrior epic piece you must clear 4-5 old-Hate mobs plus one new mob to reach the Hand (who seems to be up much more frequently, and who always drops the epic bit).  The Essence of Vampire for Enchanters is still as rare as ever, but at least now you don't have to bring a raid to clear the zone, and the repop rate of 30mins means that there are a lot more opportunities to get the drop in a given amount of time.<br><br>People who complain about the update to this zone have clearly not done their research.</p>&nbsp;<br>Poosha, Halfling Overlord<br>Nocturne Somnus, Erudian High Priest of Quellious<br>&lt;Seofon&gt; Xev</td></td></tr>
